---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Setup checklist — Mother's Gold Spice as Mom's Sole Proprietorship" description="End-to-end registration checklist for launching Mother's Gold Spice as a Sole Proprietorship in Mom's name — every form, fee, document, and timeline.">
  <main class="bg-cream min-h-screen">
    <!-- HERO -->
    <header class="border-b border-ink/10">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-spice-500 font-medium mb-4">Setup checklist · Bangalore · Mom's Sole Prop</p>
        <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-ink mb-5 leading-tight">Registering<br/>Mother's Gold Spice</h1>
        <p class="text-ink/70 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed">
          Every form, every fee, every document — for a Bangalore family business with <strong>Mom as the legal Sole Proprietor</strong> and son as the operational helper (handling digital ops, packaging, shipping on weekends). Mom owns the recipe, the kitchen, the brand. Son handles tech + delivery in evenings while keeping his IT day-job (and his separate Variolearn sole prop, registered separately under his own PAN).
        </p>
        <p class="text-ink/70 max-w-2xl text-sm mt-3">
          End-to-end: ~3 weeks of evening work (mostly done together — mom signs, son operates the laptop), ~₹6,000 in fees.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-5 text-sm">
          <a href="/plan" class="text-spice underline hover:text-spice-700">← Back to the launch plan</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- SUMMARY TABLE -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-2">At-a-glance summary</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink/60 mb-6">Every registration in the order it needs to happen. Bottom row = totals.</p>

      <div class="su-table-wrap">
        <table class="su-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>#</th><th>Registration</th><th>Mandatory?</th><th>Time</th><th>Fee</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>1</td><td><strong>Udyam (MSME)</strong></td><td>Yes — unlocks discounts elsewhere</td><td>30 min online</td><td>₹0</td></tr>
            <tr><td>2</td><td><strong>Shops & Establishments</strong> (Karnataka e-Karmika)</td><td>Yes — Karnataka law</td><td>2–3 days online</td><td>₹250–1,000</td></tr>
            <tr><td>3</td><td><strong>Business current account</strong> (HDFC / ICICI / Axis)</td><td>Yes</td><td>3–7 days</td><td>₹0–2,000</td></tr>
            <tr><td>4</td><td><strong>GST registration</strong></td><td>Yes if selling on Amazon; optional otherwise until ₹40L turnover</td><td>3–7 days online</td><td>₹0</td></tr>
            <tr><td>5</td><td><strong>FSSAI Basic Registration</strong></td><td>Yes — required to sell any food legally</td><td>3–7 days online</td><td>₹100/year (or ₹500 for 5 years)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>6</td><td><strong>Trademark (TM-A)</strong></td><td>Optional but strongly recommended</td><td>1 evening to file; 12–24 months to certificate</td><td>₹4,500 (MSME rate)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>7</td><td><strong>Shiprocket account</strong></td><td>Yes — once shipping starts</td><td>1–2 days KYC</td><td>₹0 signup + per shipment</td></tr>
            <tr class="su-table-total"><td colspan="4"><strong>Total one-time spend</strong></td><td><strong>~₹5,500–7,500</strong></td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="su-callout">
        <p class="su-callout-label">Working assumptions for this checklist</p>
        <ul class="su-bullets">
          <li><strong>Sole Proprietor (legal owner):</strong> Mom</li>
          <li><strong>All registrations use:</strong> Mom's PAN, Mom's Aadhaar, Mom's home address</li>
          <li><strong>Manufacturing premises (declared address):</strong> Mom's home (where the kitchen actually is)</li>
          <li><strong>Operational helper:</strong> Son — drives the digital paperwork, runs the website + shipping, handles customer service in evenings. Acts as Mom's authorized representative; not a partner.</li>
          <li><strong>Channel at launch:</strong> D2C only (mothersgoldspice.com + Instagram + WhatsApp) via Shiprocket</li>
          <li><strong>Time budget:</strong> ~3 weeks of evenings — mom signs, son operates the laptop. Once registered, mom cooks during the day; son handles ops on weekends.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="su-callout-amber">
        <p class="su-callout-label">Why Mom and not the son?</p>
        <p>Three reasons:</p>
        <ul class="su-bullets" style="margin-top: 6px;">
          <li><strong>The kitchen + the cook are both at her home.</strong> FSSAI license + GST registration align naturally — the address on paper is where production actually happens.</li>
          <li><strong>Lower tax bracket.</strong> Mom's slab is likely lower than the son's IT-salary slab → less total tax on combined household income.</li>
          <li><strong>Zero employer visibility.</strong> Son's IT employer can search his PAN on the GST portal — anything in his name is visible. With MGS in mom's PAN, the son's day-job stays cleanly separated from the food business. (His separate Variolearn sole prop is the only thing tied to his PAN.)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- DOCUMENTS YOU NEED -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-2">Documents you'll need (gather these first)</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink/60 mb-6">Same documents appear repeatedly across registrations. Get a single folder ready and the rest is just form-filling.</p>

      <div class="su-doc-grid">
        <div class="su-doc-card">
          <p class="su-doc-name">Mom's PAN card</p>
          <p class="su-doc-detail">Her personal PAN. Sole Proprietorship is in her name, so her PAN is the business's tax ID.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="su-doc-card">
          <p class="su-doc-name">Mom's Aadhaar card</p>
          <p class="su-doc-detail">Mandatory for OTP verification on every government portal. Must be linked to a mobile number she has access to.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="su-doc-card">
          <p class="su-doc-name">Mom's passport-size photo</p>
          <p class="su-doc-detail">JPG, ~50–200 KB. White background. Used on Shops & Est, FSSAI, Trademark applications.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="su-doc-card">
          <p class="su-doc-name">Mom's home address proof</p>
          <p class="su-doc-detail">Property tax receipt (if owned) OR rent agreement (if rented). Whoever's name is on the document — that name needs to match the applicant or have a NOC.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="su-doc-card">
          <p class="su-doc-name">Electricity bill</p>
          <p class="su-doc-detail">Latest 1–2 months for mom's home. Backup address proof — ideally in mom's name; if in dad's/spouse's name, a one-line affidavit confirms she resides there.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="su-doc-card">
          <p class="su-doc-name">NOC (if applicable)</p>
          <p class="su-doc-detail">If mom rents her home: one-page landlord NOC saying no objection to "small-scale food prep and packaging." If she owns it: skip this.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="su-doc-card">
          <p class="su-doc-name">Mom's mobile + email</p>
          <p class="su-doc-detail">Aadhaar OTP comes to her registered mobile. Create a business email she can sign into (e.g., <code>moms@mothersgoldspice.com</code> via Cloudflare email routing — free). Forward to your inbox if you're handling day-to-day replies.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="su-doc-card">
          <p class="su-doc-name">Trademark image</p>
          <p class="su-doc-detail">High-res PNG/JPG of the combined wordmark + leaf + tagline. Already designed — pull from the label-preview SVG.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="su-doc-card">
          <p class="su-doc-name">Bank cancelled cheque (mom's)</p>
          <p class="su-doc-detail">Available after mom's business current account is opened — needed for GST + Shiprocket.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- STEP 1: UDYAM -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <div class="su-step-header">
        <span class="su-step-num">1</span>
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-1">Udyam (MSME) Registration</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink/60">Free, 30 minutes online. Do this first because it unlocks the ₹4,500 MSME rate on Trademark (vs ₹9,000 standard).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="su-meta">
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Portal</span><a href="https://udyamregistration.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="su-link">udyamregistration.gov.in</a></div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Fee</span>₹0</div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Time</span>~30 minutes</div>
      </div>

      <div class="su-purpose">
        <p class="su-purpose-label">Purpose — what is it and why now?</p>
        <div class="su-purpose-grid">
          <div>
            <strong class="su-purpose-key">What it is</strong>
            <p>A free government certificate that registers mom as a "Micro Enterprise" under the MSME Development Act 2006. Replaces the older "Udyog Aadhaar" / "SSI" registration.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong class="su-purpose-key">Why do it</strong>
            <p>Unlocks the <strong>₹4,500 MSME rate</strong> on trademark filing (vs ₹9,000 standard). Also enables: priority bank loans, government tender bids, subsidies, GST schemes for small businesses, late-payment recovery under MSMED Act.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong class="su-purpose-key">What you get</strong>
            <p>A <strong>19-digit Udyam Registration Number</strong> + downloadable PDF certificate in mom's name. Used as proof of MSME status for every future government interaction.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">What you need (all in mom's name)</h3>
      <ul class="su-bullets">
        <li>Mom's Aadhaar (linked to her mobile for OTP)</li>
        <li>Mom's PAN</li>
        <li>Mom's mobile + email</li>
        <li>Business name: "Mother's Gold Spice"</li>
        <li>Self-declare turnover (₹0 currently → "Micro" category)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">Steps</h3>
      <ol class="su-step-list">
        <li>Sit next to mom with her phone (for OTP). Go to <a href="https://udyamregistration.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="su-link">udyamregistration.gov.in</a></li>
        <li>Click "For New Entrepreneurs who are not yet registered as MSME"</li>
        <li>Enter mom's Aadhaar → verify via OTP sent to her mobile</li>
        <li>Fill mom's PAN → verify</li>
        <li>Fill business details: name "Mother's Gold Spice", type (Proprietorship), address (mom's home), date of commencement, bank account (her existing personal savings account is fine temporarily — update to business current account after step 3)</li>
        <li>Self-declare investment + turnover (Micro = up to ₹1 cr investment, up to ₹5 cr turnover)</li>
        <li>Submit → Udyam Registration Number (URN) issued immediately, PDF downloadable</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="su-outcome">Outcome: <strong>Udyam Registration Certificate in Mom's name</strong>. Use this PDF on Trademark application + future tender bids + bank loans.</div>
    </section>

    <!-- STEP 2: SHOPS & ESTABLISHMENTS -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <div class="su-step-header">
        <span class="su-step-num">2</span>
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-1">Shops & Establishments Registration</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink/60">Karnataka state law. Required for any commercial activity. Bank will ask for this when opening current account.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="su-meta">
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Portal</span><a href="https://serviceonline.gov.in/karnataka" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="su-link">Karnataka e-Karmika</a></div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Fee</span>₹250–1,000 (varies by employee count; ₹0 employees for now)</div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Time</span>2–3 days</div>
      </div>

      <div class="su-purpose">
        <p class="su-purpose-label">Purpose — what is it and why now?</p>
        <div class="su-purpose-grid">
          <div>
            <strong class="su-purpose-key">What it is</strong>
            <p>A registration with the <strong>Karnataka Labor Department</strong> required by the Karnataka Shops & Commercial Establishments Act, 1961. Confirms that mom's home is being used for a registered commercial activity.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong class="su-purpose-key">Why do it</strong>
            <p>Mandatory under Karnataka law for any commercial activity. More importantly: <strong>banks require this certificate to open a business current account</strong>. Without S&E, you cannot open the bank account in the business name (step 3).</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong class="su-purpose-key">What you get</strong>
            <p>A <strong>Registration of Establishment Certificate</strong> in mom's business name, valid 5 years. Unlocks the next step (bank account) and proves legal commercial status to anyone who asks.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">What you need (all in mom's name)</h3>
      <ul class="su-bullets">
        <li>Mom's PAN + Aadhaar</li>
        <li>Photo of the establishment (a photo of mom's home door / exterior works)</li>
        <li>Address proof of mom's home: property tax receipt OR rent agreement + electricity bill</li>
        <li>Business name "Mother's Gold Spice" + nature of business (food manufacturing + retail)</li>
        <li>Number of employees (0 currently — just mom as proprietor)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">Steps</h3>
      <ol class="su-step-list">
        <li>Go to Karnataka e-Karmika portal (search "Karnataka Shops and Establishments online")</li>
        <li>Register mom as new applicant → verify her mobile + email</li>
        <li>Fill Form A: business name (Mother's Gold Spice), address (mom's home), proprietor (mom), employees (0), nature of business (Food manufacturing + retail sale)</li>
        <li>Upload mom's PAN, Aadhaar, her photo, address proof of her home</li>
        <li>Pay fee online (₹250 for 0 employees)</li>
        <li>Application submitted → certificate emailed in 2–3 days, in mom's name</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="su-outcome">Outcome: <strong>Registration of Establishment Certificate in Mom's name</strong>. Renewed every 5 years.</div>
    </section>

    <!-- STEP 3: BANK ACCOUNT -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <div class="su-step-header">
        <span class="su-step-num">3</span>
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-1">Business Current Account</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink/60">All revenue + expenses flow through this. Required for GST, Razorpay, Shiprocket.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="su-meta">
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Bank</span>HDFC / ICICI / Axis (online-friendly) or Kotak 811 Biz</div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Fee</span>₹0–2,000 opening; ₹0–500/month maintenance</div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Time</span>3–7 days</div>
      </div>

      <div class="su-purpose">
        <p class="su-purpose-label">Purpose — what is it and why now?</p>
        <div class="su-purpose-grid">
          <div>
            <strong class="su-purpose-key">What it is</strong>
            <p>A dedicated <strong>Current Account</strong> in the business's name (separate from mom's personal savings account). Current accounts are designed for high-volume business transactions — no daily withdrawal limits, no interest, supports cheques + UPI + bulk transfers.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong class="su-purpose-key">Why do it</strong>
            <p>Required for: <strong>GST registration</strong> (bank details mandatory), <strong>Razorpay onboarding</strong>, <strong>Shiprocket COD remittance</strong>, customer trust (invoices show a business account). Also creates clean accounting separation between MGS revenue and mom's personal finances.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong class="su-purpose-key">What you get</strong>
            <p>Account number + IFSC + chequebook + business debit card. Activates all the payment + collection infrastructure for the rest of the setup.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">What you need (all in mom's name)</h3>
      <ul class="su-bullets">
        <li>Mom's PAN + Aadhaar</li>
        <li>Mom's Shops & Establishments certificate (from step 2)</li>
        <li>Mom's Udyam certificate (from step 1)</li>
        <li>Address proof of mom's home (electricity bill + property tax receipt)</li>
        <li>Mom's passport photo</li>
        <li>Initial deposit (₹5k–25k depending on bank — refundable, becomes working capital)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">Recommended banks for a one-person Sole Prop</h3>
      <div class="su-table-wrap">
        <table class="su-table">
          <thead><tr><th>Bank</th><th>Account type</th><th>Min balance</th><th>Why pick</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><strong>Kotak Neo Biz</strong></td><td>Current</td><td>₹0</td><td>Fully digital onboarding, zero MAB, best for solo proprietors</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>HDFC SmartUp</strong></td><td>Current</td><td>₹10,000</td><td>Best Razorpay integration, founder-friendly</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>ICICI iStartup 2.0</strong></td><td>Current</td><td>₹10,000</td><td>Bundled with GST registration + accounting tools</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Axis Liberty for Business</strong></td><td>Current</td><td>₹0–10,000</td><td>Free first 6 months, decent app</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="su-callout">
        <p class="su-callout-label">Add son as authorized signatory</p>
        <p>When opening mom's current account, ask the bank to add the son as an <strong>authorized signatory</strong> (free, just one extra signature on the account opening form). This lets the son operate the account day-to-day — issue cheques, transfer money, link Razorpay — without mom physically visiting the bank every time. Mom remains the legal owner; son is just the operator.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- STEP 4: GST -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <div class="su-step-header">
        <span class="su-step-num">4</span>
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-1">GST Registration</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink/60">Mandatory for Amazon. Optional for pure D2C/Instagram until ₹40 lakh turnover, but get it now so all channels are open.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="su-meta">
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Portal</span><a href="https://www.gst.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="su-link">gst.gov.in</a></div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Fee</span>₹0</div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Time</span>3–7 days</div>
      </div>

      <div class="su-purpose">
        <p class="su-purpose-label">Purpose — what is it and why now?</p>
        <div class="su-purpose-grid">
          <div>
            <strong class="su-purpose-key">What it is</strong>
            <p>A <strong>15-digit Goods and Services Tax Identification Number (GSTIN)</strong> issued by the GST Council. Replaces the old VAT / service tax / excise system. Lets you charge + collect GST on sales and claim input tax credit on purchases.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong class="su-purpose-key">Why do it</strong>
            <p>Mandatory for selling on <strong>Amazon, Flipkart, Big Basket, Blinkit, Zepto</strong> — they won't open a seller account without GST. Also: lets you issue proper tax invoices (required for B2B sales), claim input-credit on jar/cap/label purchases (saves ~5% on COGS), and unlocks the full retail channel ecosystem.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong class="su-purpose-key">What you get</strong>
            <p>A <strong>15-digit GSTIN</strong> printed on every invoice (and optionally on labels). Two GST filings per quarter (GSTR-1 for sales, GSTR-3B for tax payment) — your CA handles these.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">What you need (all in mom's name)</h3>
      <ul class="su-bullets">
        <li>Mom's PAN + Aadhaar (mobile-linked for OTP)</li>
        <li>Mom's photo</li>
        <li>Business address proof: mom's home — electricity bill + property tax / rent agreement (+ NOC if applicable)</li>
        <li>Mom's bank account details: name, account number, IFSC, branch (cancelled cheque from step 3)</li>
        <li>HSN codes: <strong>2001</strong> (pickled vegetables) or <strong>2008</strong> (preserved fruits) — pick the one matching your recipe</li>
        <li>Business name: "Mother's Gold Spice"</li>
        <li>Constitution: "Proprietorship"</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">Steps</h3>
      <ol class="su-step-list">
        <li>Go to <a href="https://www.gst.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="su-link">gst.gov.in</a> → "New Registration"</li>
        <li>Fill PART A: mom's PAN, her email, her mobile → verify via OTP → receive TRN (Temporary Reference Number)</li>
        <li>Continue with TRN → fill PART B: business details, mom's home address, mom's bank, HSN codes</li>
        <li>Aadhaar e-KYC verification using mom's Aadhaar (recommended — avoids physical verification)</li>
        <li>Submit application</li>
        <li>If Aadhaar-verified: GSTIN issued in 3 working days. If not: officer may visit mom's home within 21 days</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="su-outcome">Outcome: <strong>15-digit GSTIN in Mom's PAN</strong>. Print on every invoice. Print on the jar label below FSSAI number (optional but cleaner).</div>
    </section>

    <!-- STEP 5: FSSAI BASIC -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <div class="su-step-header">
        <span class="su-step-num">5</span>
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-1">FSSAI Basic Registration</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink/60">The ₹100/year tier. No kitchen inspection. Legally unlocks selling pickle via D2C from week 2 onwards.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="su-meta">
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Portal</span><a href="https://foscos.fssai.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="su-link">foscos.fssai.gov.in</a></div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Fee</span>₹100/year (₹500 for 5 years)</div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Time</span>3–7 days</div>
      </div>

      <div class="su-purpose">
        <p class="su-purpose-label">Purpose — what is it and why now?</p>
        <div class="su-purpose-grid">
          <div>
            <strong class="su-purpose-key">What it is</strong>
            <p>A registration with the <strong>Food Safety and Standards Authority of India (FSSAI)</strong>. The "Basic" tier is for petty manufacturers with turnover up to ₹12 lakh/year — no kitchen inspection, just a self-declaration + ₹100/year fee.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong class="su-purpose-key">Why do it</strong>
            <p><strong>Legally mandatory</strong> to manufacture or sell any food in India. Without it, every jar sold is illegal under Section 31 of the FSS Act (₹5 lakh fine + 6 months imprisonment + product seizure). The 14-digit FSSAI number MUST appear on every label, every invoice, every D2C / Instagram / WhatsApp listing.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong class="su-purpose-key">What you get</strong>
            <p>A <strong>14-digit FSSAI Registration Number</strong> (prefix <code>1XXXXXXXXX</code>) in mom's name + downloadable certificate. Legal green light to start selling pickle within the ₹12L turnover cap. Customer trust signal (it's a credibility marker shoppers look for).</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">What you need (all in mom's name)</h3>
      <ul class="su-bullets">
        <li>Mom's PAN + Aadhaar</li>
        <li>Mom's photo (passport size)</li>
